title: Manhattan: 96th Street (West) - Central Park West

text:
Scotch Presbyterian Church, Central Park West at S.W. corner of 96th Street. This structure was demolished in the fall of 1928 to make way for an apartment house. July 10, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

title: Manhattan: 96th Street - Central Park West

text:
7 West 96th Street, adjoining the N.W. corner of Central Park West. This is the home of Mrs. Augusta E. Stetson, which connects with the First Church of Christ Scientist. Mrs. Stetson was the founder of this church, with direct permission both of Mother Church in Boston and Mary Baker Eddy.
May 27, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.
